---
import LegalLayout from '../layouts/LegalLayout.astro';
import Prose from '../components/Prose.astro';
import { site } from '../data/site';
---
<LegalLayout
  title="Refund Policy"
  description="Refund and billing-issue rules for future eligible Pinkflow purchases; both checkouts are closed."
  lastUpdated={site.lastUpdated.refunds}
>
  <Prose>
    <p>This Policy was last updated on {site.lastUpdated.refunds}.</p>

    <h2>1. Current purchase availability</h2>
    <p>
      Neither Namescape checkout nor Gateway.pink checkout is currently available. The prices
      published on pinkflow.ai are launch or preview information, not open purchase offers. Before
      eligible digital purchases open, this Policy and the checkout terms will be reviewed for any
      product-specific treatment.
    </p>

    <h2>2. Generally final once delivered or used</h2>
    <p>
      If Namescape purchase access opens, its search packs will be digital consumables. A paid
      search will be deducted only when an eligible action returns a usable result. A Namescape
      purchase will <strong>generally be final once delivered or used</strong>, except where
      applicable law requires otherwise or where there is a billing, delivery, or service issue
      we can correct.
    </p>
    <p>
      If Gateway.pink checkout opens, Gateway credits will be digital consumables. Credits consumed
      by a settled paid request will <strong>generally be final</strong>, except where applicable law
      requires otherwise or where there is a billing, delivery, or service issue we can correct.
    </p>

    <h2>3. Why used digital value is different</h2>
    <p>
      If a future paid search returns suggestions, verification, or availability results, that value
      cannot be returned in the same way as a physical item. We will still investigate failures,
      duplicates, unauthorized transactions, and any case where the purchased balance or result
      was not delivered as described. The same principle will apply to Gateway credits consumed by
      a settled paid request if credit checkout opens.
    </p>

    <h2>4. Statutory rights are preserved</h2>
    <p>
      Nothing in this Policy waives a non-waivable consumer right under {site.jurisdiction} law,
      EU or UK consumer law where applicable, or the law of your country of residence. If local
      law entitles you to cancellation, a refund, repair, replacement, or another remedy in your
      circumstances, that right applies.
    </p>

    <h2>5. Issues we will investigate and correct</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>You were charged more than once for the same purchase because of a technical failure.</li>
      <li>You were charged but the purchased searches were not added to your account.</li>
      <li>A paid action deducted searches but returned no usable result because the provider or service failed.</li>
      <li>Gateway credits were consumed for a request that did not settle or deliver the result described by its route contract.</li>
      <li>An unauthorized transaction appears on your account.</li>
      <li>The service was materially unavailable at purchase time and you received no value.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>6. Timing and information to send</h2>
    <p>
      Email <a href={`mailto:${site.email}`}>{site.email}</a> with your account email, transaction
      identifier, purchase date, and a short description of the issue. Please report billing
      issues within 60 days so records are readily available.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>We respond within <strong>{site.responseWindow}</strong>.</li>
      <li>We aim to resolve billing and delivery issues within <strong>{site.resolutionWindow}</strong> of the first report.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>7. Payment processor</h2>
    <p>
      Paddle processes eligible purchases as the {site.paddle.role.toLowerCase()}. Your statement
      will show <strong>{site.paddle.statementLabel}</strong>. Contact Pinkflow first so we can
      investigate the product and delivery record; we will involve Paddle when payment processing
      or a refund requires it.
    </p>
  </Prose>
</LegalLayout>
